The course introduces the legal aspects and basic principles of reclamation of mining areas in Estonia.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To provide an overview of basic principles of reclamation of mining areas in Estonia.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student who has completed the course: - is familiar with the main environmental impacts of mining and mitigation measures - is familiar with the environmental impact assessment procedure - is able to apply environmental management systems (ISO 14001 and EMAS) in managing the environmental impacts of mineral extraction - knows the technologies of organizing oil shale quarries - knows the technologies of remediation of mined areas - knows the technologies of the reorganization of natural building materials quarries and peat production areas - is familiar with water regime and vegetation restoration technologies in mined areas - is familiar with mining residues and waste and their handling - is familiar with the legislation on the regulation of mining areas - can prepare an arrangement project - is able to collect and analyze factual material collected through fieldwork in order to organize a career
